from __future__ import annotations

from event_mesh.contracts.work_item import WorkItem
from event_mesh.processors.base_processor import BaseProcessor


class PushProcessor(BaseProcessor):
    supported_channel = "push"

    def _deliver(self, item: WorkItem) -> str:
        device_token = item.payload.get("device_token", "unknown")
        message = item.payload.get("message", "no-message")
        return f"push delivered to {device_token}: {message}"

      "path": "tests/processors/test_push_processor.py",
      "content": "﻿"""Tests for PushProcessor."""

import pytest

from event_mesh.contracts.work_item import WorkItem
from event_mesh.models.ticket import Ticket
from event_mesh.processors.push_processor import PushProcessor


def test_push_processor_supports_push_channel() -> None:
    processor = PushProcessor()
    ticket = Ticket(
        ticket_id="t1",
        target_channel="push",
        data={"device_token": "tok123", "message": "hello"},
    )
    assert processor.supports(ticket) is True


def test_push_processor_rejects_non_push_channel() -> None:
    processor = PushProcessor()
    ticket = Ticket(
        ticket_id="t2",
        target_channel="email",
        data={"to": "user@example.com", "subject": "hi"},
    )
    assert processor.supports(ticket) is False


def test_push_processor_delivers_successfully() -> None:
    processor = PushProcessor()
    ticket = Ticket(
        ticket_id="t3",
        target_channel="push",
        data={"device_token": "tok456", "message": "test"},
    )
    result = processor.process(ticket)

    assert result.success is True
    assert result.processor == "PushProcessor"
    assert result.item_id == "t3"
    assert "tok456" in result.details
    assert "test" in result.details
